      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_273180_1844_06_16_page01.jpg"/>
            
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1844-06-16"/>June 16 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi>1844 </dateline>
               <note> To <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AgneE1">Elizabeth Agnew</persName><lb/>
               (Lis<unclear>g</unclear>).</note><lb/>
               <salute>
                  Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#AgneE1">Madam</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I have been for this month<lb/>
               past dangerously ill of<lb/>
               Erosepilas - otherwise you<lb/> 
               should have heard from me<lb/>
               and should have received<lb/>
               my most sincere thanks<lb/>
               for the beautiful, <choice><orig>impur-<lb/>
                  chaseable</orig><reg>impurchaseable</reg></choice> present you have<lb/>
               made me, and for the<lb/>
               Inscription so adding to
               its value and so <choice><orig>peculiar<lb/>
                  -ly</orig><reg>peculiarly</reg></choice> gratifying to me -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I presume not to praise<lb/>
               your talents for drawing<lb/>
               and for writing have been<lb/>
               so felt and so expressed<lb/>
               by the best judges and by<lb/>
               the public in general, that<lb/>
               
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_273180_1844_06_16_page02.jpg"/>
               
               the tribute of praise from<lb/>
               any individual were not<lb/>
               only superfluous but<lb/>
               must appear rather <choice><orig>imper<lb/>
               -tinent</orig><reg>impertinent</reg></choice> -<lb/></p>
               <p>- Allow me to say<lb/>
               that what I have heard of<lb/>
               you from your own family<lb/>
               with whom I have had the<lb/>
               pleasure of becoming <choice><orig>acquaint<lb/>
               ed</orig><reg>acquainted</reg></choice>, and the character of<lb/>
               your mind which I have<lb/>
               gathered from your works<lb/>
               and from your conduct<lb/>
               from your sacrifices to <del><unclear></unclear></del><lb/>
               your sense of duty and<lb/>
               aspirations after The <choice><orig>great-<lb/>
                  est</orig><reg>greatest</reg></choice> good, are altogether<lb/>
               what have interested me.<lb/>
               For you my dear<persName ref="./Personography.xml#AgneE1">Madam</persName><lb/>
               far above that admiration<lb/>
               which your talents excite<lb/>
            </p>
            
            <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_273180_1844_06_16_page03.jpg"/>
               
               <p>- However we may differ<lb/>
               in opinion, I rejoice, in<lb/>
               feeling that no exclusive<lb/>
               belief separates us from<lb/>
               each other - The last of<lb/>
               those amiable lines which<lb/>
               you have addressed to me<lb/>
               I consider as not only <choice><orig>ho-<lb/>
               norable</orig><reg>honorable</reg></choice> to your own <choice><orig>cha-<lb/>
               ritable</orig><reg>charitable</reg></choice> and liberal Faith<lb/>
               but as doing honor and<lb/>
               justice to the religion which<lb/>
               you have embraced -<lb/>
               your hope that we may<lb/>
               meet hereafter in happiness<lb/>
               proven to me that the <add>Roman</add> Catholic<lb/>
               faith does not preclude this<lb/>
               belief, and I rejoice <del/>for<lb/>
               in this conviction to which<lb/>
               I had before been inclined<lb/>
               by the assertions of some well<lb/>
                  informed <choice><orig>R</orig><reg>Roman</reg></choice> Catholics and<lb/>
                  
            <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_273180_1844_06_16_page04.jpg"/>
                  
               in which I am most happy<lb/>
               to be thus confirmed by<lb/>
               you<lb/>
              
            </p>
            <closer>
               Believe me dear<persName ref="./Personography.xml#AgneE1"><choice><orig>Ma<lb/>
                  dam</orig><reg>Madam</reg></choice></persName><lb/>
               Your much obliged<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
            </closer>
         </div>
